  "_exec_summary": [
    {
      "ESSeqNum": 0,
      "FacilityID": 1000008467,
      "SummaryText": "Tronox Pigments (Savannah), Inc. (TPS) is committed to the guiding principle of the American Chemistry Council's Responsible Care.   TPS has prepared a policy stating this commitment. TPS has aggressively implemented the Responsible Care principles into the operation.  The programs that have been developed to meet the requirements of Process Safety Management and the Risk Management Program are based on these programs.  In addition, the principles of responsible chemical manufacturing outline in PSM and RMP are practiced to a certain degree in other parts of the operation not regulated by PSM or RMP.\n\nThe products produced at the Savannah Facility are titanium dioxide pigment and sulfuric acid.  Chlorine is used in the manufacture of titanium dioxide along with the intermediate, titanium tetrachloride.  The facility has prepared a worst case scenerio for chlorine and alternative case scenerios for chlorine and titanium tetrachloride.  \n\nEven though the use of LPG (propane) is fed into process equiment as a fuel,  TPS has chosen to include it into the Risk Management Plan for maintaining some consistency in the principles applied under PSM and RMP.  As such, a worst case scenario and an alternative case scenario for propane is also included in our Risk Management Plan.\n\nTPS continues to focus on improving all aspects of its PSM and RMP program."
    }
